<P>
   BUSH-MILITARY _ AUSTIN, Texas _ At a time when the Tet Offensive
was dramatically increasing the number of young Americans in combat
in Vietnam, George W. Bush, then a congressman's kid, found a way
to put on a uniform yet stay relatively safe during the unpopular
war. How he managed to do that is a question that has dogged Bush
since he made his first run for public office six years ago, and it
continues as he pursues a front-runner's campaign for the GOP
presidential nomination. (Ward/Harmon, Austin American-Statesman)
MOVED
