<P>
   &UR; KENNEDY, JR., MISSING: &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A small plane carrying John F. Kennedy Jr., his wife, Carolyn
Bessette Kennedy, and her sister, Lauren Bessette, disappeared late
Friday, and by Saturday afternoon, the authorities had recovered
debris off Martha's Vineyard, Mass., that they said may have come
from the plane.
</P>
<P>
   We are begining to receive photos of search and rescue
operations as well as the area in Martha's Vineyard were debris has
reportedly been seen.
</P>
<P>
   Photos will move by 5:00 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   We will advise further as we have more information on photo
availability.
</P>
<P>
   Previously we have moved:
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) OFF MARTHA'S VINEYARD, Mass., A Coast Guard boat, part of
the search and rescue operation looking for John F. Kennedy, Jr.'s
plane off the southwestern coast off of Martha's Vineyard, Mass.,
on Saturday. Photo slugged: KENNEDY MISSING PLANE 3
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) WASHINGTON, Deputy Assistant Secretary of Defense for
Public Affairs Rear Adm. Craig Quigley, calls on reporters at the
Pentagon during a news conference about the search for John F.
Kennedy, Jr.'s aircraft on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Photo slugged: KENNEDY MISSING PLANE 2
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) NEW YORK, John F. Kennedy Jr., with his staff at George
magazine. A small plane carrying John F. Kennedy Jr., his wife,
Carolyn Bessette Kennedy, and her sister was reported missing on
Friday, and a huge search was under way Saturday off Long Island,
N.Y., and Cape Cod, Mass. Kennedy had obtained his pilot's license
in just the past year and acquired the aircraft recently. Photo
slug: KENNEDY MISSING PLANE
</P>
