<P>
   OLYMPICS
</P>
<P>
   OLY-RECORDS-OPEN _ ATLANTA _ In a dramatic gesture of openness,
Atlanta Olympic officials Monday will unlock the doors on a vast
and historic record of the city's Olympic experience and invite the
public in to take a look. In making available for the first time
some 5,700 boxes of documents and artifacts, Olympic officials are
releasing their longheld grip on privacy and opening the 1996
Centennial Games to microscopic scrutiny. Inside the public and
researchers likely will find the blow-by-blow, behind-the-scenes
story of the staging and organization of Atlanta's biggest event
this century. (Turner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 50. MOVED.
</P>
