<P>
   HEMINGWAY _ On the occasion of Ernest Hemingway's centennial, it
seems fitting to focus on the great writer as a sportsman. He
believed sports gave man his best chance to make the transition
from coward to courage _ and no place, he believed, was that more
evident than in the fight game. (Archdeacon, Dayton Daily News).
45.
