Days, this town turns itself into a slice of Americana now mostly
relegated to old photographs and newsreels _ flags, costumes,
friends waving at friends, and children retrieving Tootsie Rolls
from the cracks of a classic brick main street. With minor changes
in clothing and motive power, what took place here Monday could
have happened in 1910, 1940 or 1960. By JIM FISHER. Story will move
