<P>
   Y2K-PREPARE _ As the millennium approaches, businesses are
working hastily to reassure customers that they are ready for the
Y2K bug. But are they? Financial institutions such as banks and
savings and loans are one of the most prepared industries, but
other sectors, such as consumer goods and retail are not. The
government is lagging behind in preparedness too, but at least the
U.S. Treasury decided to circulate more money just in case there's
a bank run.
</P>
<P>
   By Deborah Adamson. (Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a''
national news files.)
