January 1996 file photo. Searchers swept the waters off Martha's
Vineyard on Saturday, pressing a desperate hunt for John F. Kennedy
Jr., his wife and her sister, whose plane had vanished in the
night. A piece of luggage from the plane was found off a Vineyard
beach. (James Estrin/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) (NYT14) DJAKOVICA, Yugoslavia -- July 17, 1999 --
KOSOVO-DEATH-TOLL, 7-17 -- Markers, some without names, on graves
near Djakovica. In the chaotic events in Kosovo, bodies are being
buried often without full documentation. At least 10,000 people
were slaughtered by Serbian forces during their three-month
campaign to drive the Albanians from Kosovo, according to war
crimes investigators, NATO peacekeeping troops and humanitarian
agencies. (Stephen Crowley/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
