<P>
   KENNEDY-PLANE (Boston) -- John F. Kennedy Jr., who crawled out
from under his father's Oval Office desk into a life of
tragedy-tinged celebrity, is presumed dead along with his wife and
her sister when the small plane he was piloting apparently crashes
off Martha's Vineyard. By Mitchell Zuckoff and Matthew Brelis.
PHOTO (First lede writethru; 2 takes)
